plxormod(mode)

Enter of leave xor mode. Enables erasing plots by drawing twice the same line,
symbol, etc.

mode (PLINT, input)
	enter (1) or leave (0) xor mode

----------------------------------------
pllightsource(x, y, z)

Sets position of the light source for use with plotsh3d()

x (PLFLT, input)
y (PLFLT, input)
z (PLFLT, input)
	x, y and z coordinates of light source

----------------------------------------
plotsh3d(x, y, z, nx, ny, side)

Plots a 3-d shaded representation of the function z[x][y] using colormap 1

x (PLFLT *, input)
y (PLFLT *, input)
	pointers to x and y coordinates of grid
y (PLFLT **, input)
	Pointer to a vectored two-dimensional array with set of function values
nx (PLINT, input)
ny (PLINT, input)
	Number of x and y values at which function is evaluated. 	
side (PLINT, input)
	If not zero, draw sides at plot

----------------------------------------
plotfc3d(x, y, z, nx, ny, side)

Plots a 3-d false color representation of the function z[x][y] using colormap 1

x (PLFLT *, input)
y (PLFLT *, input)
	pointers to x and y coordinates of grid
y (PLFLT **, input)
	Pointer to a vectored two-dimensional array with set of function values
nx (PLINT, input)
ny (PLINT, input)
	Number of x and y values at which function is evaluated. 	
side (PLINT, input)
	If not zero, draw sides at plot

----------------------------------------
plfill3(n, x, y) 

Pattern fills the 3d polygon bounded by the n input points x and y

n (PLINT, input)
	number of polygon vertices
x (PLFLT *)
y (PLFLT *)
	array of x and y coordinates of polygon vertices

----------------------------------------
pl_setcontlabelparam(offset, size, spacing, active)

Set offset and spacing of contour labels

offset (PLFLT, input)
	Offset of label from contour line (if set to 0.0, labels are printed on the lines).
size (PLFLT, input)
	Font height for contour labels [0..1]
spacing (PLFLT, input)
	Spacing parameter for contour labels
active (PLINT, input)
	Activate labels, default off

----------------------------------------
pl_setcontlabelformat(lexp, sigdig)

Set the format of the contour labels

lexp (PLINT, input)
	If the contour label exceed 10^(lexp) or 10^(-lexp), the exponential format is used 
sigdig (PLINT, input)
	Number of significant digits


----------------------------------------
plstripc( id, xspec, yspec, xmin, xmax, xjump, ymin, ymax, 
	xlpos, ylpos, y_ascl, acc, colbox,  collab,
        colline,  styline, legline, labx, laby, labtop )

Create a four pen strip chart, to be used aftwards by plstripa()

id (PLINT, output)
	identification of strip chart to use on plstripa() and plstripd()

xspec (const char *, input)
yspec (const char *, input) 
	x and y axis specification as in plbox()

xmin (PLFLT, input)
xmax (PLFLT, input)
ymin (PLFLT, input)
ymax (PLFLT, input)
	initial coordinates of plot box; they will change as data is added

xjump (PLFLT, input)
	x jump step(% [0..1]). When x attains xmax, xmax is set to xmax+xjump

xlposx (PLFLT, input) 
ylposy (PLFLT, input)
	x and y legend box position [0..1]

y_ascl (PLINT, input)
	autoscale y between x jumps (1) or not (0)

acc (PLINT, input)
	accumulate strip plot (1) or slide (0)

colbox (PLINT, input)
	plot box color
collab (PLINT, input)
	legend color

colline (PLINT *, input)
	array of 4 color lines for each pen
styline (PLINT *, input)
	array of 4 line styles for each pen
legline (char *[], input)
	array of 4 legends for each pen

labx (char *, input)
laby (char *, input)
	x and y axis label

labtop (char *, input)
	plot title

----------------------------------------
plstripa( id, p, x, y )

Add a point to a given pen of a given stripchart.
There is no need for all pens to have the same number of
points or beeing equally time spaced.

id (PLINT, input)
	id of strip chart
p (PLINT, input)
	pen number [0..3]
x (PLFLT, input)
y (PLFLT, input)
	x and y coordinates of point to plot

----------------------------------------
plstripd( id )

Deletes and releases memory used by a stripchart

id (PLINT, input)
	id of stripchart to delete
